markets.title: Will inflation in Euro Area be above 5% in 2022?
markets.rules_primary: If Consumer Price Index inflation in Euro Area is greater than 5% in 2022 according to the Federal Reserve Economic Data (FRED) system, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: As of Issuance, the data is expected to be released on or after February 10, 2023. Please see WCPI in the Rulebook for the legally binding terms and conditions. To access, go to FRED (at Source Agency link) and make sure the units are "Growth rate same period previous year, Not Seasonally Adjusted"
